The paper deals with data integrity scoring mechanisms in IoT networks, specifically in the presence of adversaries who manipulate the data. This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The proposed Bayesian inference model and prospect theoretic framework involve machine learning and decision-making, which are relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of simulation experiments to validate the proposed framework, which falls under the category of simulation and modeling (cs.SI). Finally, the paper involves the use of statistical models and probability theory, which are relevant to the data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category.
